<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCHOLARSHIPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Re "Minority Scholarships," Feb. 18: 
</P>
<P>
 This piece depicts how far the feds are going to promote disenfranchisement. 
Special privileges to specific groups violate the Civil Rights Act of 1964.This 
act is still a good and fair law. It prohibits discrimination for reasons of 
race, color, creed and national origin. It also violates the U.S. Constitution 
in that it doesn't authorize the feds' involvement in education or anything 
else not specified. See the 10th Amendment. 
</P>
<P>
 Secretary of Education Richard Riley's contention that minorities have been 
discriminated against is not my bone of contention. I am a first-generation 
American. I am not now or have I ever been responsible for discrimination. How 
about my rights? 
</P>
<P>
 This is how totalitarian governments promote hatred, emphasizing differences 
instead of similarities. Special privileges to specific groups achieve this 
diabolical purpose. 
</P>
<P>
 ALFRED L. NILSSON 
