<TEXT>
<P>
 The New York Rangers became the first NHL team to win 40 games this season 
with a 4-1 victory over Philadelphia Monday night in New York. 
</P>
<P>
 Winning goaltender Mike Richter, who earned his 100th NHL victory, made 25 
saves and was only beaten by Mikael Renberg's fluke goal with 6:11 left in the 
game.Renberg's turnaround wrist shot deflected off Ranger defenseman Jeff 
Beukeboom and bounced into the net. 
</P>
<P>
 Winnipeg 3, San Jose 3 -- Alexei Zhamnov's power-play goal with 9:11 left in 
the third period at Winnipeg enabled the Jets to tie the Sharks and end a 
club-record 10-game losing streak. But the Jets are still winless in their last 
19 games (0-16-3). 
</P>
<P>
 San Jose is 0-4-1 in its last five. 
</P>
<P>
 Pittsburgh 4, Florida 3 -- Rick Tocchet's second goal of the game with 4:40 
left in the third period led the Penguins over the Panthers at Miami. Mario 
Lemieux, playing in only his ninth game of the season, had a goal and two 
assists. 
</P>
<P>
 New Jersey 5, St. Louis 1 -- Bill Guerin scored two goals to lead the Devils 
over the Blues in East Rutherford, N.J. 
</P>
<P>
 Toronto 4, Ottawa 1 -- Wendel Clark scored three goals as the Maple Leafs beat 
the Senators in Ottawa. 
