<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOY ATHLETE OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kristian Vallas 
</P>
<P>
 Servite, Sr. 
</P>
<P>
 Basketball / Forward 
</P>
<P>
 When the Friars need points, they know to go to Vallas. Friday, he scored 10 
of his game-high 19 points in the fourth quarter to lead Servite to a 47-46 
victory over Sonora, top-seeded in Division III-AA.Trailing by one with 30 
seconds to play, Servite got the ball to Vallas, who drove the lane and was 
fouled with three seconds remaining. He made the first free throw, Sonora 
called time out to disrupt his concentration, and then he made the second. He 
also had 22 points and nine rebounds in a 66-57 victory over Magnolia last 
week. Other notables: 
