NEWSWIRE: TENNESSEE'S HOUSTON QUITS VOLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Wade Houston, Tennessee's basketball coach, has resigned with the Vols (5-19 
overall and 1-12 in the Southeastern Conference) apparently destined for their 
worst season since they finished 4-19 in 1961-62. 
</P>
<P>
 Houston said he will leave after this season.The Vols have two regular-season 
games left before the Southeastern Conference tournament in two weeks. 
</P>
<P>
 Houston, whose five-year record at Tennessee is 65-87, said he hopes to 
continue coaching. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Louisiana State has always required that inductees into the school's hall of 
fame have a college degree, but LSU's athletic council voted 9-1 to allow 
exceptions, thus paving the way for Shaquille O'Neal and the late Pete 
Maravich. Names in the News 
