<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: VENICE; HIGH SCHOOL 
TEAM WINS REGIONAL SCIENCE BOWL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For the second consecutive year, a team from Venice High School has taken 
first place in the regional competition of the National Science Bowl. 
</P>
<P>
 Venice High last weekend beat 19 high school teams -- 15 from the Los Angeles 
Unified School District. The five-member team from Venice will travel to 
Washington on April 22 to challenge 50 regional finalists in the national 
competition. 
</P>
<P>
 A team from University High School in Los Angeles came in second, and Van Nuys 
High School placed third. 
</P>
<P>
 The program is sponsored by the U.S. Department of Energy and local sponsors 
including Arco, Rockwell, the California Energy Commission and the Los Angeles 
Department of Water and Power. 
</P>
</TEXT>
