<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: CYPRESS; CITY ASKING FOR HELP TO BUY TREES FOR PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city and the Friends of Cypress Recreation and Parks are seeking donations 
for trees during the fourth annual Tree Donation Project. 
</P>
<P>
 A $100 donation will buy a 2-foot-tall tree, $175 will buy a 2 1/2-foot tree, 
$300 will buy a 3-foot tree and $500 will buy a 3 1/2-foot tree. 
</P>
<P>
 The trees will be planted at the former Texaco/Chestnut Park in April, when 
the park will be officially rededicated as the Darrell Essex Park, in honor of 
the city manager. 
</P>
<P>
 Each donation will be recognized with a plaque to be placed at the foot of the 
tree with the name of the donor. 
</P>
<P>
 All donations must be made by March 18. 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress has been recognized for its protection and conservation programs for 
trees and is a member of the National Arbor Day Foundation. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 229-6780.MIMI KO 
