<HEADLINE>
<P>
SERVICES PENDING FOR LAWYER WHO DIED IN FALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Funeral services are pending for William A. Wittman Jr., a well-known attorney 
who died last week of injuries suffered in an accidental fall in Puerto 
Vallarta. He was 60. 
</P>
<P>
 A longtime resident of Newport Beach, Wittman graduated from Newport Harbor 
High School, where he was student body president and played varsity football 
and competed on the varsity track team. At Pomona College, where he studied 
pre-law, he was a starter on two conference championship football teams and was 
president of Kappa Delta fraternity. 
</P>
<P>
 After graduation, he served several years in the U.S. Army as a first 
lieutenant. He graduated from Stanford University law school, and moved back to 
the Newport Beach area in 1962 and began his law practice. 
</P>
<P>
 Wittman was involved in many community activities, including the Newport 
Harbor Exchange Club, where he was a past president, Newport Beach Athletic 
Club, Newport Beach Tennis Club, Newport Harbor Area Chamber of Commerce and 
Orange County Bar Assn. 
</P>
<P>
 He is survived by his father, William Wittman Sr., four children, Christine 
McBride, Kelly Wittman, Laurie McCracken and William Wittman; two brothers, 
Steve and Randy Wittman; one sister, Barbara Wittman Searles; and four 
grandchildren. 
</P>
<P>
 Funeral services are being arranged by Pacific View Memorial Park in Newport 
Beach. In lieu of flowers, his family requests that donations be made to the 
Newport Harbor Exchange Club's child-abuse-prevention program and to the 
Newport Harbor High School football program. 
</P>
