EAST VALLEY FOCUS: NORTH HOLLYWOOD; POLICE SEEK SUSPECT IN SLAYING AT PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHAU LAM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police are looking for a gunman who fatally shot a Glendale man and wounded 
two others as they were watching a soccer game in a North Hollywood park over 
the weekend. 
</P>
<P>
 Alejandro Garzon, 36, of Glendale was taken to North Hollywood Medical Center 
where he died less than an hour after Sunday's 4:20 p.m. shooting near Tujunga 
Avenue and Magnolia Boulevard, said Los Angeles Police Lt. Ron LaRue of the 
North Hollywood station's homicide division. 
</P>
<P>
 LaRue said Garzon was shot once in the chest as he sat watching a soccer 
match. 
</P>
<P>
 Two other men believed to be Garzon's friends, both of Los Angeles, were 
treated for minor gunshot wounds at an undisclosed hospital, said LaRue. 
Authorities declined to name the two men. 
</P>
<P>
 "We don't have a motive and we don't have any suspects," LaRue said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police are asking anyone with information about the shooting to call 989-8831. 
CHAU LAM 
