<TEXT>
<P>
 New Jersey's political Establishment turned out in force to denounce bigotry 
in anticipation of a speech by a controversial member of the Nation of Islam. 
But Khallid Abdul Muhammad offered a more subdued message than expected before 
an audience of about 350 at Trenton State College, his first public speaking 
