<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: UCLA'S WILLIAMS OUT FOR SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Natalie Williams' college career ended when the two-sport UCLA star learned 
Monday she has a serious knee injury requiring surgical repair. 
</P>
<P>
 Williams, an All-American in basketball and volleyball, suffered a torn 
anterior cruciate ligament when she injured her right knee during a 
UCLA-Stanford basketball game Saturday at Palo Alto. 
</P>
<P>
 Williams, a senior forward from Taylorsville, Utah, is the Pacific 10 
Conference's leading scorer (23.4) and rebounder (13.1). She also is the 
Pac-10's all-time rebound leader with 1,137. 
</P>
<P>
 UCLA team orthopedist Gerald Finerman indicated he was optimistic she could 
return to sports after a post-surgery rehabilitation program. EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
