<P>
 Star TV, Hong Kong's Wharf Cable Sever Agreement: Asian satellite broadcaster 
Star TV has ended its agreement with Hong Kong-based Wharf Cable for the latter 
to retransmit Star TV's programming. The decision is significant because it 
will probably make it more difficult for Star TV to launch a pay TV channel in 
Hong Kong, one of the most lucrative markets in Asia, because Wharf Cable is 
set to become the largest cable TV system in the world.Star TV, which was taken 
over by Rupert Murdoch in July, has been embroiled in a legal dispute with 
Wharf since January. Under the agreement, Star TV was to be the exclusive 
provider to Wharf Cale for all English-language programming in Hong Kong. 
