</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 IHOP Corp., the Glendale franchiser and operator of International House of 
Pancakes restaurants, reported strong gains in profits for its fourth quarter 
and year ended Dec. 31. 
</P>
<P>
 In the fourth quarter, IHOP earned $4.46 million, up 59% from $2.81 million in 
net income a year before. Its revenue in the quarter rose 15%, to $38.6 million 
from $33.7 million a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 For all of 1993, the company had a profit of $10.7 million, a 35% increase 
from a $7.93 million profit in 1992. Last year its annual revenue grew 25%, to 
$142.5 million from $114 million the year before. 
</P>
<P>
 IHOP said the results reflected its growth strategy. The company opened 64 new 
restaurants last year. 
