<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: WARNER CENTER PROPERTIES ARE DIVIDED BY PARTNERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Woodland Hills real estate developer Robert D. Voit said he and several 
partners of a joint venture that built 40 buildings in Warner Center agreed to 
divide up their ownership of the properties. 
</P>
<P>
 The properties include six office towers and the Warner Center Marriott Hotel. 
The last of them opened three years ago. 
</P>
<P>
 Voit said the venture partners had been discussing how to restructure the 
development's ownership since then. Previously, the joint venture owned the 
entire development. 
</P>
<P>
 Voit owns 18 buildings in Warner Center Business Park, including offices and 
retail stores, under the new agreement. Voit will also continue to manage all 
40 buildings developed by the joint venture. 
</P>
