REGIONAL ROUNDUP: BENTON OIL INCREASES STAKE IN JOINT VENTURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Benton Oil and Gas Co., an Oxnard energy concern, said it has acquired an 
additional 30% interest in its Venezuelan joint venture, Benton-Vinccler, for 
$3 million cash, $10 million in promissory notes and 200,000 shares of Benton 
common stock. 
</P>
<P>
 The purchase brings Benton's share of the oil-drilling venture to 80%. The 
company also said that Benton-Vinccler has refinanced $15 million of commercial 
paper, which served as project debt financing. 
</P>
<P>
 Benton-Vinccler is reactivating and developing three oil fields in Venezuela 
with proved reserves of 78 million barrels of oil. Benton said the venture 
successfully tested its first horizontal well in one of the fields. 
</P>
