<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: NEW OWNER TAKES OVER WEST HILLS MEDICAL CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 West Hills Regional Medical Center and Los Robles Regional Medical Center in 
Thousand Oaks have a new owner following the mega-merger of Columbia Healthcare 
Corp. and HCA-Hospital Corp. of America. 
</P>
<P>
 The merger between Columbia of Louisville, Ky., and Nashville, Tenn.-based HCA 
created a new company, Columbia/HCA Healthcare Corp., one of the world's 
largest health-care providers. 
</P>
<P>
 Besides the West Hills and Los Robles medical centers, Columbia/HCA now owns 
192 hospitals and other medical facilities in the U. S., England and 
Switzerland. 
</P>
<P>
 Previously, Columbia owned the West Hills center and HCA-Hospital owned the 
Los Robles center. 
</P>
