<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: DICK CLARK PRODUCTIONS SEES 2ND-QUARTER PLUNGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dick Clark Productions Inc. said its fiscal second-quarter net income plunged 
87%, even though its revenue more than doubled compared with the same period a 
year ago. 
</P>
<P>
 In the quarter that ended Dec. 31, the Burbank producer of television shows 
reported net income of $164,000, down from $1.2 million in 1992's fiscal second 
quarter. Revenue surged to $12.7 million from $5.4 million, however. 
</P>
<P>
 For the six months, the company's net income fell 49% to $595,000 from $1.2 
million in last year's first half. Revenue rose 80% to $26.4 million from $14.7 
million in the year-earlier period. 
</P>
