REGIONAL EARNINGS: HARMONY HOLDINGS LOSS SOARS ON RESTRUCTURING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Harmony Holdings Inc., a Burbank producer of television commercials and music 
videos, reported that its losses widened in its latest quarter and six months, 
partly due to a $500,000 restructuring charge. 
</P>
<P>
 In its fiscal second quarter ended Dec. 31, Harmony lost $1.19 million, in 
contrast with a year-earlier loss of $372,636. Its revenue rose 58%, to $9.53 
million from $6.1 million. 
</P>
<P>
 Harmony's six-month loss was $1.99 million, more than double the $769,920 loss 
in the year-ago period. Its revenue was $19.7 million, a 93% gain from $10.2 
million in revenue a year before. 
</P>
