<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: WESTERN NATIONAL ACQUIRES KEMPER APARTMENT PORTFOLIO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Western National Group, Orange County's largest apartment developer and 
manager, said it has acquired the entire apartment portfolio of Kemper 
Residential Management for an undisclosed sum. 
</P>
<P>
 Western's first nationwide acquisition adds 17 apartment complexes with 3,419 
units to its holdings, bringing its total apartments under management to 
27,000, the company said.The apartments are located in nine states: California, 
Florida, Georgia, Missouri, Mississippi, Oregon, South Carolina, Texas and 
Washington.  
</P>
<P>
 The employees at Kemper, a property management firm based in Lafayette, in 
Northern California, will join Western National, the company said. 
</P>
<P>
 "This expands our portfolio under management by more than 12%," said Don 
Vodra, managing partner of Western National Group. "We expect it to increase 
our exposure to similar medium- and large-scale opportunities with 
institutional investors, asset managers and property managers." 
</P>
</TEXT>
