</P>
<P>
 The world's first license plates were introduced by the Paris police in France 
in 1893. 
</P>
<P>
 License plate No. 8 was sold at a Hong Kong government auction for the 
equivalent of about $602,250 on Feb. 13, 1988, to Law Tingpong, a textile 
manufacturer. The number 8 is considered a lucky number. Car Collection 
</P>
<P>
 The unrivaled collector of Rolls-Royces was Bhagwan Shree Rajneesh the Indian 
mystic of Rajneeshpuram, a commune in Oregon. His disciples presented him with 
93 of the expensive British automobiles before his deportation from the United 
States in November, 1985. 
</P>
<P>
